    title: 'What is an Abscessed Tooth and How is it Treated?',
    slug: 'abscessed-tooth-treatment',
    question: 'I have severe pain and swelling in my mouth. My dentist mentioned I might have an abscessed tooth. What exactly is this and what treatment options are available?',
    answer: 'An abscessed tooth is a serious dental condition that occurs when bacteria invade the dental pulp, causing infection and pus formation. This typically happens due to untreated tooth decay, gum disease, or dental trauma.\n\nSymptoms include severe throbbing pain, swelling of the face or gums, sensitivity to hot and cold, fever, and a bad taste in the mouth.\n\nTreatment options include:\n\n1. **Root Canal Treatment**: The most common and effective treatment that removes infected pulp and seals the tooth\n2. **Dental Extraction**: If the tooth cannot be saved\n3. **Antibiotics**: To control infection before definitive treatment\n4. **Drainage**: In severe cases, the abscess may need to be drained\n\nAt Indira Dental Clinic, we use modern techniques and equipment to ensure comfortable treatment. Early intervention is crucial to prevent complications like bone loss or systemic infection.\n\nI recommend scheduling an appointment immediately if you suspect an abscess, as this condition can worsen quickly and may require emergency treatment.',
