    answer: 'Dental implants are designed to be a permanent solution for missing teeth, with an impressive success rate and longevity when properly cared for.\n\n**Expected Lifespan**:\n- **Implant Fixture**: 25+ years, often lifetime with proper care\n- **Crown/Restoration**: 10-15 years, may need replacement due to wear\n- **Overall Success Rate**: 95-98% over 10+ years\n\n**Factors Affecting Longevity**:\n1. **Oral Hygiene**: Regular brushing, flossing, and professional cleanings\n2. **Bone Quality**: Adequate bone density and volume\n3. **Systemic Health**: Conditions like diabetes can affect healing\n4. **Lifestyle Factors**: Smoking significantly reduces success rates\n5. **Regular Maintenance**: Professional checkups every 6 months\n\n**Maintenance Requirements**:\n- Excellent oral hygiene routine\n- Regular dental checkups\n- Avoiding excessive force (no ice chewing, nail biting)\n- Professional cleanings to prevent gum disease\n\nAt Indira Dental Clinic, we use premium implant systems and provide comprehensive aftercare instructions. Our patients typically enjoy their implants for decades with proper maintenance.\n\nI recommend scheduling a consultation to assess your specific situation and discuss the best implant options for your needs.',
