    slug: 'root-canal-treatment-pain',
    question: 'I need a root canal treatment but I\'m terrified of the pain. Is it really as painful as people say?',
    answer: 'This is one of the most common concerns I hear from patients, and I\'m happy to clarify this misconception.\n\n**The Reality**: Modern root canal treatment is much more comfortable than its outdated reputation suggests.\n\n**Pain Management**:\n- **Local Anesthesia**: Complete numbing of the affected area\n- **Advanced Techniques**: Rotary instruments for faster, more comfortable treatment\n- **Sedation Options**: Available for anxious patients\n- **Post-Treatment Care**: Prescribed medications for any discomfort\n\n**What to Expect**:\n1. **During Treatment**: You should feel no pain, only pressure\n2. **After Treatment**: Mild discomfort for 2-3 days, manageable with over-the-counter pain relievers\n3. **Healing Process**: Gradual improvement over 1-2 weeks\n\n**Why the Misconception Exists**:\n- The pain people associate with root canals is usually the infection that necessitated the treatment\n- Root canal treatment actually **relieves** pain, not causes it\n- Outdated techniques from decades ago created this false reputation\n\n**Our Approach at Indira Dental Clinic**:\n- State-of-the-art equipment for comfortable treatment\n- Experienced team focused on patient comfort\n- Clear communication throughout the procedure\n- Comprehensive aftercare instructions\n\nRemember, untreated dental infections can cause severe pain and complications. Root canal treatment is often the most comfortable solution to eliminate pain and save your tooth.',
