    id: '4',
    title: 'What Causes Gum Disease and How Can I Prevent It?',
    slug: 'gum-disease-prevention',
    question: 'My dentist mentioned I have early signs of gum disease. What causes this condition and what can I do to prevent it from getting worse?',
    answer: 'Gum disease (periodontal disease) is a common but preventable condition that affects the supporting structures of your teeth.\n\n**Causes of Gum Disease**:\n1. **Poor Oral Hygiene**: Inadequate brushing and flossing allows plaque buildup\n2. **Tobacco Use**: Smoking significantly increases risk\n3. **Genetics**: Some people are more susceptible\n4. **Systemic Conditions**: Diabetes, heart disease, and hormonal changes\n5. **Medications**: Certain drugs can affect gum health\n6. **Nutritional Deficiencies**: Lack of vitamin C and other nutrients\n\n**Early Signs (Gingivitis)**:\n- Red, swollen, or tender gums\n- Bleeding during brushing or flossing\n- Bad breath that persists\n- Receding gum line\n\n**Prevention Strategies**:\n1. **Excellent Oral Hygiene**:\n   - Brush twice daily with fluoride toothpaste\n   - Floss daily to remove plaque between teeth\n   - Use antimicrobial mouthwash\n\n2. **Regular Professional Care**:\n   - Dental cleanings every 6 months\n   - Early detection through regular checkups\n   - Professional scaling when needed\n\n3. **Lifestyle Changes**:\n   - Quit smoking\n   - Maintain a balanced diet\n   - Manage stress levels\n   - Control systemic conditions\n\n**Treatment Options**:\n- **Early Stage**: Professional cleaning and improved home care\n- **Advanced Stage**: Scaling and root planing, antibiotic therapy\n- **Severe Cases**: Surgical intervention or laser therapy\n\nAt Indira Dental Clinic, we provide comprehensive periodontal care and work with you to develop a personalized prevention plan. Early intervention is key to maintaining healthy gums and preventing tooth loss.',
