    id: '5',
    title: 'When Should Wisdom Teeth Be Removed?',
    slug: 'wisdom-teeth-removal-timing',
    question: 'I\'m 18 and my dentist recommended wisdom teeth removal. When is the best time to have this procedure done?',
    answer: 'Wisdom teeth removal is a common procedure, and timing is crucial for optimal outcomes.\n\n**Optimal Timing**:\n- **Age Range**: 16-22 years old is generally ideal\n- **Root Development**: When roots are 1/3 to 2/3 formed\n- **Before Problems Develop**: Proactive removal prevents complications\n\n**Why Early Removal is Better**:\n1. **Easier Extraction**: Roots are less developed, making removal simpler\n2. **Faster Healing**: Younger patients typically heal more quickly\n3. **Reduced Complications**: Less risk of nerve damage or bone loss\n4. **Preventive Care**: Avoids future problems like impaction or infection\n\n**Signs You Need Removal**:\n- **Impacted Teeth**: Teeth that don\'t emerge properly\n- **Crowding**: Wisdom teeth pushing other teeth out of alignment\n- **Infection**: Recurring gum infections around wisdom teeth\n- **Cavities**: Difficulty cleaning leading to decay\n- **Pain**: Discomfort from pressure or inflammation\n\n**Recovery Process**:\n- **Initial Healing**: 3-5 days for initial recovery\n- **Complete Healing**: 2-3 weeks for full recovery\n- **Pain Management**: Prescribed medications and ice packs\n- **Diet**: Soft foods for the first few days\n\n**Our Approach at Indira Dental Clinic**:\n- Comprehensive evaluation with X-rays\n- Comfortable sedation options\n- Experienced oral surgery team\n- Detailed aftercare instructions\n- Follow-up care to ensure proper healing\n\nI recommend scheduling a consultation to evaluate your specific situation. Early removal often results in a smoother procedure and faster recovery.',
